WEBVTT

1
00:01:11.200 --> 00:01:13.259
<i>October 7, 2007.</i>

2
00:01:14.337 --> 00:01:16.271
<i>Four days till we deploy.</i>

3
00:01:17.573 --> 00:01:20.565
<i>Grace knows I would do anything
to get back to her.</i>

4
00:01:21.277 --> 00:01:22.471
<i>Anything.</i>

5
00:01:25.114 --> 00:01:27.139
<i>Today I wrote her a letter.</i>

6
00:01:38.794 --> 00:01:42.423
Good afternoon, sir. I have the briefing
papers from the colonel's office.

7
00:01:42.565 --> 00:01:44.294
Put them on the desk.

8
00:01:48.771 --> 00:01:50.033
Thank you, Corporal.

9
00:01:56.646 --> 00:01:58.443
Major. Hey.

10
00:01:59.882 --> 00:02:01.782
Hope you don't have to deliver it.

11
00:02:03.452 --> 00:02:04.476
Copy that.

12
00:02:04.887 --> 00:02:06.616
- Be safe out there, Sam.
- Thanks, sir.

13
00:02:06.756 --> 00:02:08.986
- See you when you get back.
- All right.

14
00:02:17.099 --> 00:02:18.396
How's this?

15
00:02:18.534 --> 00:02:19.592
Warm.

16
00:02:23.539 --> 00:02:24.870
- Hello.
- Dad!

17
00:02:25.007 --> 00:02:27.066
Hey! Hey, baby.

18
00:02:27.210 --> 00:02:28.370
- Hi, Daddy.
- How you doing?

19
00:02:28.511 --> 00:02:30.172
- How was school?
- Great.

20
00:02:31.247 --> 00:02:34.375
They gave me Noodles the dog.
She's in my room.

21
00:02:36.018 --> 00:02:37.315
Izzie?

22
00:02:38.888 --> 00:02:40.185
Hey.

23
00:02:41.023 --> 00:02:43.218
- What's wrong?
- Nothing.

24
00:02:43.960 --> 00:02:45.894
What's wrong, honey?

25
00:02:46.028 --> 00:02:47.757
You're leaving again.

26
00:02:48.698 --> 00:02:50.359
Come give your daddy a hug.

27
00:02:51.067 --> 00:02:51.999
No.

28
00:02:53.069 --> 00:02:54.900
Come on. Give me a kiss, honey.

29
00:02:55.037 --> 00:02:56.197
Just go.

30
00:02:56.772 --> 00:02:59.104
- Two kisses?
- No.

31
00:03:00.076 --> 00:03:01.475
Three kisses?

32
00:03:02.144 --> 00:03:04.009
I wanna read my book.

33
00:03:04.146 --> 00:03:06.080
You wanna read your book?

34
00:03:07.717 --> 00:03:08.945
Oh, yeah?

35
00:03:10.987 --> 00:03:15.924
I see a smile coming. There it is! There it is!
Now, you're getting 100 kisses!

36
00:03:16.092 --> 00:03:19.493
- Behind you! Right behind you!
- What? What? What? Who? Who?

37
00:03:20.763 --> 00:03:24.665
Wait a second! Two against one.
That is no fair!

38
00:03:24.834 --> 00:03:26.324
Daddy, put me down!

39
00:03:26.469 --> 00:03:27.401
Girls.

40
00:03:28.304 --> 00:03:31.432
- Come on. Daddy's gotta go.
- Okay.

41
00:03:31.574 --> 00:03:35.010
Please stay. Please let him stay.

42
00:03:35.144 --> 00:03:38.705
- Yeah. Can't you stay?
- It's my brother.

43
00:03:38.848 --> 00:03:40.679
He doesn't deserve you.

44
00:03:42.285 --> 00:03:44.412
Go rob another bank, Tommy!

45
00:03:44.887 --> 00:03:47.185
Bring that money back to me, brother!

46
00:03:56.332 --> 00:03:57.765
See you later.

47
00:04:22.024 --> 00:04:24.083
What happened to my little brother?

48
00:04:35.304 --> 00:04:36.566
No fucking way.

49
00:04:59.161 --> 00:05:01.891
You ever think of
apologizing to that woman?

50
00:05:04.600 --> 00:05:05.862
It's green.

51
00:05:06.702 --> 00:05:07.896
I got it.

52
00:05:20.249 --> 00:05:22.240
So, what are you gonna do?

53
00:05:22.385 --> 00:05:27.687
I don't know. I'm just gonna
cash this check, and then who knows.

54
00:05:28.224 --> 00:05:30.059
- I'll see you later?
- Yeah, all right. All right.

55
00:05:30.159 --> 00:05:32.719
- Don't rob the place.
- Yeah. Get the fuck out of here.

56
00:05:47.643 --> 00:05:49.543
No hot water in this place?

57
00:05:51.447 --> 00:05:53.347
Fucking hot water is missing.

58
00:06:01.257 --> 00:06:02.349
I'm sorry.

59
00:06:02.525 --> 00:06:04.652
How do you stand this kitchen?

60
00:06:05.227 --> 00:06:07.661
He didn't expect to be deploying again
so soon.

61
00:06:07.797 --> 00:06:09.526
Yeah. Well, are you ripping your hair out?

62
00:06:09.665 --> 00:06:11.963
What are you gonna do?
They call, you answer.

63
00:06:12.101 --> 00:06:13.693
- Don't tell her. Oh, no.
- Yes!

64
00:06:13.836 --> 00:06:15.736
- I won.
- She got you, Granddad.

65
00:06:15.871 --> 00:06:17.771
You're raising a real hustler here, Grace.

66
00:06:17.907 --> 00:06:19.238
I know.

67
00:06:24.313 --> 00:06:25.940
My birthday's this spring.

68
00:06:26.081 --> 00:06:28.515
It is, isn't it?
What is it, March 10th, something like that?

69
00:06:33.189 --> 00:06:34.747
- Hi.
- Hi.

70
00:06:34.924 --> 00:06:37.449
- Are you Isabelle?
- No, I'm Maggie.

71
00:06:37.626 --> 00:06:39.116
Isabelle's big.

72
00:06:40.362 --> 00:06:41.886
I'm Tommy.

73
00:06:42.064 --> 00:06:43.554
Mom doesn't like you.

74
00:06:43.732 --> 00:06:44.824
Maggie!

75
00:06:44.967 --> 00:06:47.333
What? That's what you said to Dad.

76
00:06:48.571 --> 00:06:50.402
These are for your mom.

77
00:06:51.941 --> 00:06:53.431
Mom, they're for you.

78
00:06:53.576 --> 00:06:54.838
Thank you.

79
00:06:55.611 --> 00:06:56.771
Come in.

80
00:06:59.181 --> 00:07:01.012
- Hey. Hi, sweetie.
- Hey.

81
00:07:01.150 --> 00:07:02.674
Come here.

82
00:07:03.652 --> 00:07:04.676
Hi.

83
00:07:05.054 --> 00:07:06.453
You made it.

84
00:07:07.790 --> 00:07:08.779
Yeah.

85
00:07:12.361 --> 00:07:13.623
- Son.
- Sir.

86
00:07:17.333 --> 00:07:19.494
- What? Hi.
- Hi.

87
00:07:19.635 --> 00:07:22.502
Bless us, O Lord, in these thy gifts
which we are about to receive

88
00:07:22.638 --> 00:07:24.572
from thy bounty through Christ,
our Lord. Amen.

89
00:07:24.707 --> 00:07:25.935
- Amen.
- Amen.

90
00:07:26.075 --> 00:07:30.444
And this is a very special meal for us
because we are welcoming one son home,

91
00:07:30.579 --> 00:07:33.446
and we're sending another one off.

92
00:07:33.582 --> 00:07:37.848
And we ask you, Lord, to keep him safe
and bring him back really soon. Right?

93
00:07:37.987 --> 00:07:38.976
- Yeah.
- Amen.

94
00:07:39.121 --> 00:07:40.452
- Amen.
- Amen.

95
00:07:41.123 --> 00:07:42.613
Here. You can do it.

96
00:07:42.791 --> 00:07:44.554
- You wanna try?
- Thank you, Mom.

97
00:07:44.727 --> 00:07:47.161
- Here, let me.
- Thanks, Mama.

98
00:07:48.964 --> 00:07:50.226
Carrots are delicious.

99
00:07:57.706 --> 00:08:00.766
- Why aren't you eating your peas?
- I hate peas.

100
00:08:02.411 --> 00:08:03.673
I do, too.

101
00:08:04.680 --> 00:08:06.705
Honey, eat your peas.

102
00:08:06.849 --> 00:08:07.781
Okay, Dad.

103
00:08:07.917 --> 00:08:09.248
I like peas.

104
00:08:10.085 --> 00:08:11.518
So do I.

105
00:08:11.654 --> 00:08:13.884
- When are you leaving?
- Tuesday.

106
00:08:17.192 --> 00:08:19.217
You love it over there, huh?

107
00:08:20.829 --> 00:08:22.194
It's my job.

108
00:08:22.331 --> 00:08:24.458
They only shoot the bad guys.

109
00:08:25.067 --> 00:08:26.796
Who are the bad guys?

110
00:08:29.038 --> 00:08:30.505
The ones with the beards.

111
00:08:34.376 --> 00:08:36.241
Your brother's a hero.

112
00:08:36.779 --> 00:08:40.271
He's serving his country,
and don't you ever forget that.

113
00:08:42.985 --> 00:08:45.317
Will you be here for my birthday?

114
00:08:46.155 --> 00:08:48.089
You know I will, sweetie.

115
00:08:49.725 --> 00:08:51.645
Sarah Miller's dad wasn't there
for her birthday.

116
00:08:51.894 --> 00:08:54.226
- Isabelle.
- It's true.

117
00:08:54.363 --> 00:08:56.923
She had to bring him a cake in prison.

118
00:08:58.200 --> 00:09:00.532
It's not just military families.

119
00:09:00.669 --> 00:09:03.263
There's a lot of folks under pressure
these days.

120
00:09:04.239 --> 00:09:06.969
They got problems in all walks of life.

121
00:09:08.444 --> 00:09:11.311
Every family's got
their own set of problems.

122
00:09:13.916 --> 00:09:15.315
They sure do.

123
00:09:19.188 --> 00:09:21.315
What is that supposed to mean?

124
00:09:25.327 --> 00:09:27.852
Every family has their own set of problems.

125
00:09:28.030 --> 00:09:30.260
You sound like a damn parrot.

126
00:09:30.399 --> 00:09:31.661
Like a what?

127
00:09:31.800 --> 00:09:34.564
Why don't you try mimicking your brother
for a change?

128
00:09:34.703 --> 00:09:35.931
Dad.

129
00:09:37.573 --> 00:09:40.098
This food is great, Elsie. Thank you.

130
00:09:41.977 --> 00:09:43.535
Compared to what?

131
00:09:48.617 --> 00:09:49.982
Other food.

132
00:09:50.119 --> 00:09:51.643
Prison food?

133
00:09:51.787 --> 00:09:52.879
Tommy!

134
00:09:59.461 --> 00:10:00.723
Excuse me.

135
00:10:05.934 --> 00:10:07.060
It's okay, honey.

136
00:10:07.202 --> 00:10:09.295
- No. No.
- It's his first night out.

137
00:10:09.438 --> 00:10:13.704
He comes waltzing in here
with no regard for anybody else.

138
00:10:13.842 --> 00:10:15.901
Doesn't even bother to apologize...

139
00:10:31.226 --> 00:10:32.887
Stay out of trouble.

140
00:10:35.564 --> 00:10:36.826
All right.

141
00:10:41.437 --> 00:10:43.803
You be safe over there. All right?

142
00:10:56.385 --> 00:10:58.080
This thing's not coming off.

143
00:10:59.021 --> 00:11:01.615
- Try more soap.
- Yeah.

144
00:11:01.790 --> 00:11:03.223
Almost got it.

145
00:11:07.529 --> 00:11:08.996
There we go.

146
00:11:11.266 --> 00:11:13.894
- Don't lose that.
- I'll do my best.

147
00:11:14.036 --> 00:11:15.230
Okay.

148
00:11:17.840 --> 00:11:21.071
- Take a lot of pictures when I'm gone.
- I always do.

149
00:11:25.781 --> 00:11:27.078
I love you.

150
00:11:27.916 --> 00:11:29.440
I love you, too.

151
00:11:59.047 --> 00:12:00.105
Sam?

152
00:12:02.351 --> 00:12:03.909
Take me with you.

153
00:12:05.621 --> 00:12:06.645
Sure.

154
00:12:10.692 --> 00:12:13.490
How about I go and you stay with the kids?

155
00:12:16.131 --> 00:12:17.257
Okay.

156
00:12:21.403 --> 00:12:22.836
Don't go.

157
00:12:29.178 --> 00:12:30.873
<i>October 12, 2007.</i>

158
00:12:31.780 --> 00:12:34.180
<i>Back in Afghanistan with my men.</i>

159
00:12:37.486 --> 00:12:40.853
<i>Weird. It almost feels like home.</i>

160
00:13:18.160 --> 00:13:20.390
Hi, Cassie. Joe Jr. is so big.

161
00:13:43.652 --> 00:13:45.119
What's the distance to the LZ?

162
00:13:45.254 --> 00:13:48.280
We're three minutes out.
Clear to detach to the LZ.

163
00:13:48.457 --> 00:13:49.481
Roger that.

164
00:13:56.498 --> 00:13:58.932
<i>Clear to engage. Weapons hot.</i>

165
00:13:59.234 --> 00:14:02.431
<i>Target took cover in the valley.</i>

166
00:14:02.571 --> 00:14:03.765
Little bastards...

167
00:14:41.310 --> 00:14:42.800
Who is it?

168
00:14:42.945 --> 00:14:46.005
It's Captain Sanderson and Chaplain Davis.

169
00:14:49.551 --> 00:14:50.483
Hi.

170
00:14:52.955 --> 00:14:55.150
- Hi. Is your mother home?
- Yeah.

171
00:14:57.326 --> 00:14:58.725
Where is she?

172
00:14:59.361 --> 00:15:00.760
In the bath.

173
00:15:03.332 --> 00:15:05.459
Would you call her for us, please?

174
00:15:09.905 --> 00:15:11.338
What's wrong?

175
00:15:14.076 --> 00:15:15.270
Izzie.

176
00:15:16.211 --> 00:15:18.076
- Okay.
- Bye.

177
00:15:32.694 --> 00:15:34.161
Come in.

178
00:16:08.764 --> 00:16:12.325
<i>You've reached Captain Sam Cahill.
Please leave a message.</i>

179
00:16:19.541 --> 00:16:23.102
<i>You've reached Captain Sam Cahill.
Please leave a message.</i>

180
00:16:39.161 --> 00:16:40.594
Grace.

181
00:16:42.431 --> 00:16:44.865
Sorry. I didn't mean to wake you.

182
00:16:47.002 --> 00:16:48.282
I was just dropping off the car.

183
00:16:48.403 --> 00:16:51.804
Sam told me I could borrow it
whenever I wanted, so...

184
00:16:53.041 --> 00:16:57.137
The taillight's a little busted.
Some asshole...

185
00:17:02.617 --> 00:17:04.312
Look, you know...

186
00:17:06.054 --> 00:17:07.489
Just say it, you know what I mean?
All right.

187
00:17:07.589 --> 00:17:10.422
He told me I could borrow the car
whenever I wanted, Grace.

188
00:17:10.592 --> 00:17:12.060
You look at me with this pissed-off look.

189
00:17:12.160 --> 00:17:13.593
Sam's dead.

190
00:17:16.998 --> 00:17:18.397
They crashed.

191
00:17:19.734 --> 00:17:22.760
- What are you talking about?
- He's dead, Tommy.

192
00:17:23.371 --> 00:17:25.202
Come in, come in.

193
00:17:31.613 --> 00:17:33.774
I don't wanna fucking come in.

194
00:17:35.684 --> 00:17:37.948
I just came here to drop off...

195
00:17:38.787 --> 00:17:42.052
- Why didn't you call me?
- I've been trying to call you all night.

196
00:17:42.224 --> 00:17:46.126
- Why didn't anybody call me?
- We've all been trying, Tommy.

197
00:17:47.829 --> 00:17:49.057
Okay.

198
00:17:52.767 --> 00:17:54.727
- Why'd you let him go over there, Grace?
- Tommy.

199
00:17:58.006 --> 00:18:00.065
For what now, huh?

200
00:18:17.325 --> 00:18:18.952
Tommy, come inside.

201
00:18:20.962 --> 00:18:23.396
I just had to sit down for a second.

202
00:18:31.106 --> 00:18:33.939
He's with your mama now. They're together.

203
00:19:06.041 --> 00:19:07.201
Drink?

204
00:19:10.078 --> 00:19:11.067
No.

205
00:19:42.777 --> 00:19:44.802
Girls? You ready?

206
00:19:45.914 --> 00:19:48.439
Yeah, in about just one minute.

207
00:19:50.218 --> 00:19:53.415
- Why'd you take your dress off?
- I hate it.

208
00:19:54.823 --> 00:19:57.792
We're going to put it on, okay?
We have to go.

209
00:19:58.193 --> 00:19:59.683
I don't want to.

210
00:20:01.096 --> 00:20:04.065
I don't want to wear mine either. It's itchy.

211
00:20:18.680 --> 00:20:20.511
Okay, come here. Okay.

212
00:20:21.383 --> 00:20:22.816
Come here.

213
00:20:27.889 --> 00:20:30.983
- Okay.
- Is Dad really dead like your mom and dad?

214
00:21:20.742 --> 00:21:22.767
- I'm sorry.
- I appreciate it.

215
00:21:31.853 --> 00:21:34.447
- I'm so sorry, dear.
- Thanks for coming.

216
00:21:35.490 --> 00:21:37.924
Sir, your son's the best damn Marine
I ever commanded.

217
00:21:38.093 --> 00:21:39.526
I appreciate it.

218
00:21:42.931 --> 00:21:44.398
- Come on, girls.
- Coming, Grandpa.

219
00:21:44.566 --> 00:21:46.431
- Get in the car.
- Come on, Maggie.

220
00:21:46.568 --> 00:21:49.093
- Elsie, I'm sorry for your loss.
- I'll watch them.

221
00:21:49.237 --> 00:21:50.329
Okay.

222
00:21:50.472 --> 00:21:55.409
Grace, Sam wrote this for you before he left.
He never wanted me to have to deliver it.

223
00:22:01.616 --> 00:22:03.584
I don't believe it, John.

224
00:22:04.452 --> 00:22:06.010
I can't feel it.

225
00:22:07.722 --> 00:22:09.952
Shouldn't I be able to feel it?

226
00:22:10.925 --> 00:22:14.827
It's hard to accept.
He was a good friend, a good Marine.

227
00:22:16.631 --> 00:22:19.498
- Why don't you let me drive?
- What are you talking about?

228
00:22:19.634 --> 00:22:22.000
- Come on, girls.
- Coming.

229
00:22:22.871 --> 00:22:25.135
Hey, why don't you give me the keys, Dad?

230
00:22:25.273 --> 00:22:27.073
What makes you so responsible
all of a sudden?

231
00:22:29.144 --> 00:22:30.702
Let Tommy drive.

232
00:22:30.845 --> 00:22:33.177
"Let Tommy drive." Look, I'll tell you what.

233
00:22:33.314 --> 00:22:35.544
Why don't you get a job
and earn some money,

234
00:22:35.683 --> 00:22:36.809
buy yourself a car,

235
00:22:36.951 --> 00:22:39.920
and then you can drive it
wherever the hell you want.

236
00:22:40.054 --> 00:22:41.544
Give me the keys.

237
00:22:44.125 --> 00:22:47.754
Did you hear those Marines in there today
talking about your brother?

238
00:22:47.929 --> 00:22:49.123
Did you?

239
00:22:50.165 --> 00:22:54.534
Who is gonna stand up and testify for you
once you're dead?

240
00:22:55.670 --> 00:22:59.401
Yeah, it's my fault Sam's dead. Right?
That's what you think.

241
00:23:00.909 --> 00:23:03.434
It's got nothing to do with you. Right?

242
00:23:04.379 --> 00:23:07.177
- What are you saying to me?
- Hank.

243
00:23:10.785 --> 00:23:11.717
Forget it.

244
00:23:12.787 --> 00:23:14.584
You never had any guts.

245
00:23:14.722 --> 00:23:16.314
And you did.

246
00:23:16.958 --> 00:23:18.860
That's why you screamed at Mom
every fucking night.

247
00:23:18.960 --> 00:23:21.554
That's why you drove us drunk, huh?
"Hang in there, Marines."

248
00:23:21.729 --> 00:23:25.062
- Don't. Come on.
- Why you put all that shit in his head.

249
00:23:25.200 --> 00:23:27.327
- You could never fill his shoes.
- I know that.

250
00:23:27.469 --> 00:23:29.994
- Never could make me proud.
- For Lord's sake.

251
00:23:30.138 --> 00:23:31.765
That is a sin.

252
00:23:31.906 --> 00:23:35.342
- Stop it. Give me the keys.
- Here you go. I'm walking.

253
00:25:07.168 --> 00:25:08.897
This is a nightmare.

254
00:25:10.371 --> 00:25:11.895
What's going on?

255
00:25:12.473 --> 00:25:14.703
What are they gonna do with us?

256
00:25:17.011 --> 00:25:18.410
That yours?

257
00:25:19.347 --> 00:25:20.371
Yeah.

258
00:25:21.082 --> 00:25:22.549
That your wife?

259
00:25:23.284 --> 00:25:24.683
Cassie, yeah.

260
00:25:26.387 --> 00:25:27.820
